# IMPORTANT consult only if you want to modify settings
Flashing our pre-configured program from the **latest release** will get this setup running in just a few minutes.  
Following the steps below is **ONLY** necessary if you want to modify parameters or customize the configuration.

# VeNFLoPi: Raspberry Pi 4B + Arducam OV5647 Setup

# Materials
- Raspberry Pi 4B  
- MicroSD card (16 GB)  
- USB-C power cable  
- Arducam 5MP OV5647 camera (Pi CSI port; check ribbon orientation)  
- Micro-HDMI cable to HDMI capture card  
- HDMI capture card to desktop PC  
- Desktop PC with OBS installed  
- Ethernet cable  
- Keyboard, Mouse, Monitor  

---

# 1) Flash OS on microSD card
Download [Raspberry Pi Imager](https://www.raspberrypi.com/software/).  
Insert microSD, select OS → Raspberry Pi OS (Legacy, 32-bit, Bookworm) → Flash.  

---

# 2) Configure Raspberry Pi
Connect to WiFi

# 3) Configure Arducam in Boot Firmware
sudo nano /boot/firmware/config.txt

Paste:

dtparam=audio=on
camera_auto_detect=1
display_auto_detect=1
auto_initramfs=1
max_framebuffers=2
disable_fw_kms_setup=0
disable_overscan=1
arm_boost=1

[cm4]
otg_mode=1

[cm5]
dtoverlay=dwc2,dr_mode=host

[all]
dtoverlay=arducam
dtoverlay=arducam-motor i2c_bus=1,i2c_addr=0x0c
start_x=1
gpu_mem=128
dtoverlay=vc4-fkms-v3d
hdmi_force_hotplug=1
hdmi_group=2
hdmi_mode=85
hdmi_drive=2
hdmi_enable_4kp60=0
disable_overscan=1
max_framebuffer_width=1280
max_framebuffer_height=720

Save (Ctrl+O → Enter) and exit (Ctrl+X).
Reboot: sudo reboot
Check: fbset -s

# 4) Install and verify camera apps
sudo apt update
sudo apt install -y libcamera-apps v4l-utils
which rpicam-hello
which rpicam-vid
rpicam-hello
rpicam-hello --version

# 5) Create camera preview script
sudo nano /usr/local/bin/cam_preview.sh

Paste:

#!/usr/bin/env bash
export DISPLAY=:0
export XAUTHORITY=/home/loganlab/.Xauthority
sleep 5
xset s off
xset -dpms
xset s noblank
WIDTH=1280
HEIGHT=720
FPS=60
/usr/bin/rpicam-vid --width $WIDTH --height $HEIGHT --framerate $FPS --fullscreen -t 0 --codec h264

# Make executable
sudo chmod +x /usr/local/bin/cam_preview.sh
sudo -u pi /usr/local/bin/cam_preview.sh

#6) Add Squid button (shutdown)
sudo nano /home/pi/squid_button.py

Paste:

from button import Button
import time
import os

btn = Button(3)  # GPIO3 / Pin 5

while True:
    if btn.is_pressed():
        time.sleep(0.2)
        os.system("sudo shutdown -hP now")
        break
    time.sleep(0.1)

# Make executable
sudo chmod +x /home/pi/squid_button.py
sudo nano /etc/rc.local

Add before exit 0:

sudo python3 /home/pi/squid_button.py &

# Button wiring:
# GPIO17 (BCM17, pin 11) → one leg
# GND (pin 6) → other leg
# Short press safely shuts down the Pi.

## 7) Create systemd service for camera
sudo nano /etc/systemd/system/cam_preview.service

Paste:

[Unit]
Description=Camera HDMI preview for capture
After=graphical.target network.target
Wants=graphical.target

[Service]
Type=simple
User=pi
Environment=DISPLAY=:0
ExecStart=/usr/local/bin/cam_preview.sh
Restart=always
RestartSec=3
StandardOutput=journal
StandardError=journal

[Install]
WantedBy=graphical.target

# Enable and start
sudo systemctl daemon-reload
sudo systemctl enable cam_preview.service
sudo systemctl start cam_preview.service
sudo systemctl status cam_preview.service
sudo journalctl -u cam_preview.service -f

## 8) Disable screen blanking permanently
sudo sed -i '$ a @xset s off\n@xset -dpms\n@xset s noblank' /etc/xdg/lxsession/LXDE-pi/autostart
sudo reboot

